n shared carbonyl and nitrile feedstocks, but some steps are overstated as direct or selective.", "approved": false, "problematic_reactions": ["rxn_002", "rxn_003", "rxn_005"], "suggestions": ["Use glycolaldehyde in a documented cyanosulfidic homologation sequence if it is intended as a true pathway intermediate.", "Revise the HCN production step to a realistic atmospheric, photochemical, or reservoir-release route.", "Clarify whether the aldol chemistry is intended as a selective synthesis or as part of a complex mixture."]}, {"pathway_id": "P3", "reaction_scores": {"rxn_001": 0.86, "rxn_002": 0.55, "rxn_003": 0.18, "rxn_004": 0.74, "rxn_008": 0.6, "rxn_009": 0.9, "rxn_010": 0.92}, "chemical_feasibility": 0.68, "pathway_coherence": 0.73, "environmental_progression": 0.85, "target_achievement": 0.94, "overall_confidence": 0.74, "feedback": "This pathway attempts to capture the Sutherland-style cyanosulfidic route and correctly identifies valine nitrile as a key convergence point. However, the specific condensed step from HCN plus glycolaldehyde plus ammonia directly to valine nitrile is too coarse and not sufficiently grounded in the staged homologation chemistry described in the literature, where UV, H2S, copper photoredox cycles, and iterative nitrile chemistry matter. Thus the route is directionally aligned with the literature but mechanistically oversimplified. Downstream nitrile hydrolysis to valine is strong.", "approved": false, "problematic_reactions": ["rxn_003", "rxn_008"], "suggestions": ["Decompose the cyanosulfidic route into explicit iterative homologation steps with H2S, UV, and Cu photoredox mediation.", "Avoid representing valine nitrile formation as a one-step conversion from glycolaldehyde unless supported directly.", "Include phosphate-buffered neutral surface conditions if invoking Sutherland-type chemistry."]}, {"pathway_id": "P4", "reaction_scores": {"rxn_001": 0.86, "rxn_002": 0.55, "rxn_003": 0.18, "rxn_005": 0.52, "rxn_006": 0.88, "rxn_007"